text:
happy #dayofthegirl! there’s a lot of discussion right now on how we can give more power to women and marginalized people with the one year anniversary of #metoo. 
i believe that it starts before the board rooms, university educations and job interviews. it starts with self esteem and young women believing in everything they are capable of. 
working with @fastandfemale over the past few years has given me a platform to start making the difference i want to see. it connects elite athletes with girls between 8-18 and shows them the benefit of sport on self esteem, goal setting and power. 
i’m very excited to bring an event to my backyard at rim park this sunday. i’m bringing in a squad of some of the athletes who have inspired me like @laurianegenest44 @a.walshie @hzunic14 @erinmcclure1 and more! if you have a young girl in your life who would be interested, there are 24 hours left to sign up! the link is in my profile! the event is in partnership with @ringetteontario will be covered by @cbcnews and there are amazing gifts each of the girls will be taking home. 
no matter how you are celebrating today, thank you for making a difference. 🙏 ❤️

text: #dayofthegirl #defynormal neither of us is 'normal'; entirely unique and molded from individual experiences. when i was a new mum, i whispered naive promises to them in their ears: 'no one will ever hurt you; i'll be the best mum; i will give you all the tools you need, your life will be easier than mine,' and so on. these are impossible promises because life happens to us all and challenges like discrimination, inequality and #metoo happen to them. but each in their own way, dazzles me with their brilliance and so i am left with my final promise: you will be brave and strong and i will always believe in you. xx. p.s. i was pregnant when i got married ;)

text: “my experiences with sexual harassment at my retail job ranges from verbal to physical, [but] most of what i deal with is verbal and it comes from men of all ages. i’ve come to almost expect it from teens to middle-aged men, but the most surprising was from a much older man, around late 70s. as i walked to the register to ring up him and his wife, he looked me up and down and said “ohhh, sexy” with a leering smile... i was so angry because i didn’t feel like i could stand up for myself for fear of my job or having worse reactions from the customer which could escalate the situation.” — anonymous, 22 #nodickpics #timesup #metoo #endsexualharassment #nomeansno #instaactivist #nofilter #instaxphoto #feminist #wontstayquiet #wontbeavictim #iamasurvivor #iamasurvivornotavictim #breakthesilence #endsexualassault #endsexualabuse #sexualassault #sexualharassment #staywoke #activist

text:
#metoo  #messiah @louisfarrakhan explains why we must elevate the woman: "if we are going to make a change on the earth. if the kingdom of god is going to come to the earth, it will be birthed through a woman and this is why mary is exalted. 
she’s not exalted because god wants you to worship her.  she’s exalted because it is only when the woman is exalted that you can bring onto to the earth the kingdom of god. 
bear with me now. since the honorable #elijahmuhammad said that #communism will be the stepping stone to the kingdom of #god; the kingdom of islam. then if you look at communism and you look at capitalism they are fighting against the rise of #islam. it was former president nixon who said. “that the real threat to democracy is not communism it is fundamentalist islam,” this is nixon talking. 
what is islam? islam is obedience to the will of god. why do they seek to put a cover over farrakhan? 
it is because they don’t want you to be attracted to the majestic power of the old time religion, the religion of #jesus, the religion of the prophets; the religion of god when he originated the heavens and the earth. 
it was islam, it is not a new religion, it is as old as god himself. obedience to his will is the way he created the heavens and the earth. he set the sun out there and said obey. he set the moon out and said obey, he created man and said obey if it pleases you. 
he gave you and me the free will to reject or accept. 
if we reject we reject to our own detriment. if we accept we accept for our own betterment. we don’t add to allah nor can we take away. he is allah self glorified. he said the heavens and the earth glorify him, he don’t need our praise. he’s worthy of praise if we never praised him, everything in creation bears witness and even in our rebellion we bear witness to his majesty." #farrakhan : how to give birth to a god pt3﻿
please send donations to either $doomalert or paypal.me/doomalert 
#shriners #masons

text:
hard to believe that this was me 5 or so years ago... - *note, at this time i was bullied at school, still hadn’t come to terms with being raped as a child, a close friend of mine tried to take her life, i had severe anger issues and was extremely violent, i was studying for my gcse’s and used to wear extra layers of clothing to make myself look bigger because i was so self conscious.* -

but how much of that would you have been able to tell just from looking at that photo? - 
things are not always as they seem, and no matter how happy someone looks, please remember... that person you just took this piss out of might be going through one of the toughest times of their life so please please please

be kind ❤️ #mentalhealth #positivity #metoo #positivevibesonly #maxout

text:
as some of you may know, my sets for @friskyradio are theme based and reflect current issues. my shows are generally challenging to put together however, my latest mix was by far the most difficult.

as a survivor of sexual abuse as a child and a young teen, i was deeply moved by christine blasey ford's testimony. her courage strengthened countless women and made it clear that our government incorrectly handled a sexual abuse victim. a one week trial to get to the bottom of what happened to her is a slap in the face to all those sexually abused: man, woman, and child alike.

today's episode recognizes all of the brave individuals who spoke out about their traumatic experiences. the system is riddled with countless injustices and the only way we can change that is by demanding it.

i will no longer stand in the shadows, feeling ashamed for something that was beyond my control. i am strong and i know that i am not alone. #metoo #sexualabuse #sexualassault #injustice #fightforchange #reflections #friskydeep #deep

text: this year has been a journey of self growth and development in a way i’ve never experienced before. i’ve felt completely lost at times. i’ve felt broken and unworthy or love or appreciation. i’ve brought past trauma to the surface and have begun to work through it in a productive way. i’ve had to lean on those who are close to me and ask for help, two things that i struggle with. i’ve realized goals i’ve had for years aren’t want i want in life anymore and have made big changes to align my life with what is most important to me. what i’ve realized during these hard and scary times is that i am strong. i am resilient. i am not alone. i am one of many who share the same trauma, the same strength, the same voice. i’ve found the courage to be true to myself. today is #internationaldayofthegirl with a focus this year on overcoming adversity. while i acknowledge my privilege in life and know that there are those who struggle in different sometimes harder ways than i do, i wanted to share my story of growth on a day that celebrates the amazing girls/women out there who overcome adversity in big ways everyday. keep fighting the fight, use your voice and your vote, we are all in this together ❤️ #internationaldayofthegirl #metoo #womenempowerment

text:
#metoo #messiah @louisfarrakhan teaches "in the united states, which is one of the most advanced societies presently on the earth, women are looked upon as "play-things". in an advanced society women are looked upon as play-things. 
how advanced then can that society be?  in europe, the woman is looked upon again as a play thing. how advanced then can that society be?

many parts of the islamic world, although we pay lip service to the great liberation effort of prophet muhammad we relegate women to roles in society or no roles in society and we relegate them to a less than human position in many of the islamic states around the country and in many cultures women are definitely oppressed.  so how advanced can this world be if the leaders of the world have denigrated the position of woman and if those so called primitive societies have not elevated the woman then the nations of the world are depressed, oppressed, and suppressed. and the greatest oppression and suppression is the suppression and oppression fomented by ignorance.

now the honorable elijah muhammad, a man born among us; a man that we believe is the messenger of god. 
a man that worked to reform us for 44 years while he was among us, said these words: “no nation can rise any higher than its women.” i’m going to say that again. 
no nation can rise any higher than its women. 
what was elijah muhammad 
saying?

if a nation wants advancement, you must exalt the woman. 
if you want to go to the heights that god intends for a nation to rise, then you must exalt the woman.

why exalt the woman? 
because if the woman is exalted; and by exalted we don’t mean putting her on a pedestal, or as in some primitive societies worshiping the woman. 
what we are saying is the exaltation of women actually means allowing them to be what god has created them to be. 
now the holy qur’an teaches us to reverence the womb of the woman; reverence of the womb that bore you. 
if we reverence the womb, that 
means we should develop a feeling or attitude of deep respect love, and awe; as for something sacred." #farrakhan  pt3﻿

text: #this calling all of our men to stick up for the women they love in these trying times.  you see us as equal, you see as valid, you see us as potent, you see the important roles we play in your lives and in larger society.  so please, if you interact with a person without the awareness to see this, please help educate them.  it will take women and men alike to fight the dated patriarchy that still has a suffocating grip in our country. it’s 2018, let’s act like it, and we need your help.  we need your help to raise the next generation of children, especially boys, that will value and live lives based in gender equality.  thank you to my husband @troutfondler for being this kind of man, i love you. #genderequality #glassceiling #femaleempowerment #believeher #women #believesurvivors #metoo #youtoo #womensrights #whoruntheworld #girls #love #marriage #challenge #goals #men #partnership #growth #loveyou #downwithpatriarchy #utah #walkthewalk #internationalgirlsday

.
.

text:
1/5 women in the usa will be raped.
1/71 men will be raped
1/10 women will be raped by an intimate partner
8/10 cases the victim knew their attacker
91% of sexual assault victims are women.. 9% are men
81% of women and 35% of men report short or long term impacts such as ptsd
1/4 of girls and 1/6 of boys will be sexually abused before they turn 18.
34% of people who sexually abuse a child are family members
12.5% of women were 10 years or younger before first rape. 30% were 11-17
28% of men were 10 or younger at their first rape
over 1/3 or women who reported being raped before 18 experienced it again.
96% of people who sexually abused kids are male.
77% of people who sexually abused kids are adults
1/5 of women and 1/16 of men are sexually assaulted in college.
over 90% of college sexual assault victims don’t report it.
63.3% of men at a university who self-reported rape/attempted rape admitted to commiting repeat rapes
rape is the most under-reported crime 
63% of sexual assaults are not reported to police
12% of child sexual abuse is reported to authorities
prevalence of false reporting is between 2% - 10%
.
.
.
there’s a false narrative that victims come forward (especially after years later) to get money, publicity or tear apart families and lives. this is not it. society has brainwashed us into thinking things like this is our fault. no matter how drunk you were, what you were wearing, if you were dating or what you said to “provoke them” does not give them your choice in what you wanted to do. no means no. whether it was a nod of a head, the vibe that you didn’t want to or even if you changed your mind. they should respect you for that decision. this should never define you in any way, shape or form. no one deserves to feel as if they have been left and abandoned by everything they had ever loved. i stand with you and so do many others. #istandwithford #believesurvivors #believewomen #timesup #metoo

text: tomorrow, at ku in rm. 310 is the #metoo teach-in. drop-in hours are from 2:00-5:00pm. this teach-in focuses on a campus response to the national dialogue around sexual assault. topics for discussion will include: the kavanaugh hearings and the implications for the us supreme court; gender norms and cultures of sexual violence; views from catholic social teaching; and a focus on the ud campus context. this format will encourage open and respectful conversations led by ud faculty and staff. all are welcome!

text:
i wanted to photograph the burn scars in lamoille canyon, but i couldn't get anywhere close to it
.
took option b and covered quite a bit of ground. all uphill so i'm definitely feeling it.  i can feel the bits of bullet in my thigh when that cold wind blows
.
made it near the crest but a storm came in and pushed me down. overhead the entire time such beautiful, varying skies and cloud formations. it turned windy and cold and purple and i'm glad i dipped out when i did. i'm amazed i have that kinda stamina, considering i don't do any aerobic exercises
.
all unedited

text:
my two cents on #metoo movement:
#3 
metoo movement is highly becoming a gender issue after the ford-kavanaugh row. out of it has arisen another movement appearing to address men’s views on sexual assault incidents. it is the #himtoo movement, also started by woman who posted her son peter hanson’s picture on twitter claiming that the metoo movement has made her son unwilling to go on “solo dates” with women.
this reminds me of my mother who is always (from her experience in the police department, she says) suggesting me to stay away from two things in particular--- drugs and girls. from drugs because they are injurious to health and girls because they may make false allegations against me of doing bad things to her. and these suggestions are given to me in punjabi which sounds hilarious. 
peter turned up against his mom saying that he will not support #himtoo and he respects and believe women. my reaction on my mother’s suggestion is somewhat same. but, only future will tell  how many men come up with their truth about false allegations against them on the internet and take this himtoo movement to the same level as that of metoo movement 
on one hand, the metoo movement has done and is doing so good, by giving voice to the women who are sexually harassed, spreading awareness about what is sexual harassment, what a woman should do if it happens and building pressure to improve the currently insufficient law system so as to better address this sensitive issue. on the other hand, it is appearing to turn into a controversy where false accusation cases are coming to light, is appearing to fail in delivering justice when limited to a social platform only and giving rise to an apparently opposing #himtoo movement which may turn the twitter into a gender battle ground. (be a nice critic)
(views are personal)

آيا تا به حال به اين كلمه دو حرفى كوچك دقت كرده ايد ؟! در نوشتار كوچك اما در واقعيت به قدر ى بزرگ كه زندگى كه نمى شود ناديده گرفتش زنان در دنيا بخش اصلي جوامع را تشكيل مى دهند و بايد با اين موضوع  كنار آمد كه كاملاً با مردان برابرند  وحتىٰ گاهى از مردان سرترند و اگر بيش از پيش به آنها بها داده شود كارهاى بزرگى كه ما مردان پر ادعا از انجام آنها باز ميمانيم را به راحتى انجام مى دهند ميشل اوباما در همين راستا كمپينى راه اندازى كرده است و چهره هاى مطرح با او همگام شده اند كه در اين ويديو قسمتى از آنا را مي بينيم.

@showontonight 
@davidbeckham 
when girls receive an education, amazing things start to happen! poverty goes down. economies grow. families get stronger. babies are born healthier. and the world, by all accounts, gets better. that’s why on the international #dayofthegirl, i’m proud to join @michelleobama and the @globalgirlsalliance to stand up for adolescent girls’ education. join us— because the future of our world is only as bright as our girls. #globalgirlsalliance

text:
no one ever asks what made you gain weight.
.
i never thought i’d be brave enough to share this part of my life.
.
though this is painful to share, i know we are stronger when we talk about our struggles-and i hope you will share yours with me below. (#metoo)
.
when i was 21 i was slipped a date-rape drug. 
the remaining details are not significant to my story, but something was taken from me that night that i’ll never get back.
.
the final words i was left with were “i only gave you what you deserved”...which were words that pierced my heart and mind for many years to come.
.
what i...deserved???
.
i immediately turned to food for comfort. honestly, the more weight i gained-the safer i felt. i felt like if i was overweight, no one would find me attractive and i wouldn’t ever get hurt again.
.
but the weight that i carried pierced much deeper.
.
instead of dealing with it, i tucked it away in my mind and hoped i would never have to face it. i started eating my feelings instead...
.
the sad reality is: 1 in 6 women will be a victim of sexual assault/rape. and it’s something we don’t talk about. at least i didn’t for many years. it was a secret i hid from the world because i felt so ashamed.
.
nobody is deserving of that. nobody. and it took me many years to fully believe that.
.
i didn’t take care of myself anymore...
i didn’t love myself anymore...
food was the only comfort that i had...
the thought of taking it away made me uncomforable.
.
but i took my life back...and so can you.
.
i share this with you, because i know i’m not alone. many of us had an event that triggered us to gain weight. but the beautiful thing is: you have the power within you to overcome it.
.
we are not defined by our past. 
we are not what had happened to us. 
we have the power to design a bright future and never look back. 
we have nothing to be ashamed of.
.
our trials can become our triumphs.
our tests can become our testimony. 
our messes can become our message.
.
and i know that if i can overcome my struggles...so can you.❤️️️️️
cc: @weightlosshero

text:
happy international day of the girl 2018!!! this international day of the girl, plan international canada is calling on canadians to join us to defy normal.

to mark international day of the girl, plan international canada has partnered with nanos research to release new national survey data that explores the lived experiences of girls 14- to 24-years-old in canada today.

one year after the start of the #metoo movement, the data reveals just how ‘normal’ sexual harassment, gender discrimination and insecurity continue to be for girls across canada.

today, we celebrate defiant girls – those who dare to defy normal each day and fight for girls’ rights and gender equality. #defynormal #internationaldayofthegirl #metoo #girlpower #jeanaugustinecentre #plancanada #planinternational

text:
why you look at that, i may have chipped a nail.
.
.
october is domestic violence awareness month.  my parents love each other until my dad passed in 1999.  like any marriage there are great happy moments and some tough times.  it takes the love and support of those who care and are trusted upon to deal and move from tough incidents. 
as in any abusive relationship the abuser always yearn for that control.  one of the proudest moments i have of my dad was when i first saw him cried not out of physical pain, but he was torn by the hurt that his "control" was causing on my mom, sister, and myself.  he humbled himself and apologize.  he recognized why he wanted that control. 
whether or not his reason legitimatize his actions is another story and month (mental health awarness). but all this to say that not only do we support the victim, but also show love /support of the accused abuser to heal as well so this won't happen again or the pattern stops.  throughout the process cannot condone their abusive behavior. 
we must stop this mess!
.
.

text:
today is international day of the girl, which is a day that promotes girls empowerment while also acknowledging the challenges we face as girls and women and how we can/are/will overcome them! this is one of the reasons i’m so passionate about giving back to the female youth golf community! 🏌🏻‍♀️🏌🏼‍♀️🏌🏽‍♀️⁣
⁣
golf has given me opportunity, taught me life lessons, and given me life long relationships that have helped mold me into who i am today. i want to be a role model to young girls to show them the possibilities of what they can achieve, and to instill in them that the possibilities are endless 🏆 these girls are going to be the future that continue to close the wage gap, who stand up for the girls who don’t feel safe to say #metoo. these girls are future  congresswomen, lpga golfers, and mothers if they choose to be 💕⁣
⁣
ladies. encourage each other. love each other. be kind and compassionate. being a female is a challenge all in itself and we need each other in our corners 💪🏼 #internationaldayofthegirl #girlpower #lpgagirlsgolf

text:
world mental health day... (i am aware this was yesterday but mental health is everyday) 
many of you may know this about me already, some of you may not. but as it is world mental health day (it was yesterday) i think it’s important to share... in june this year i came to the end of my most recent therapy. which i have had continuously for two and a bit years. a proud moment... since the age of 15, (i am now 26) i have had the following mental health conditions, anorexia, exercise-bulimia, i have binged eaten, anxiety, depression, and two years ago our family change when we found out that my mother was donor conceived, meaning that we have a whole extra family. (for anyone that is donor conceived you may know yourself that this can bring up a whole plethora of reasonable and explainable mental heath issues) i also have unfortunately experienced #metoo. 
for myself the journey to wellness there has not been one specific resolution, it has taken time, persistence, hard work and patience and love from those closest to me. 
i have had numerous different types of therapy each in there own right important at the time had it, giving myself new insight and enabling me to learn more, this has included; hypnotherapy, an eating disorder nurse, a mentor, a dyslexic tutor, a nutritionist, art therapy, personal trainer, a therapist, workplace dyslexic tutor and a another different counsellor/therapist, for a v short period antidepressants, self-help books, holistic therapy, and support from charities.

friends and family have been a huge part of my recovery and continue to do so, from sending me pictures of normal meals, allowing me to write essay anxiety thought texts with no judgement attached, making sure i ate, sitting patiently while i sobbed or was stuck with fear, encouraging me to socialise, sending of quotes, and endless re rationalising my irrational thought process, to people whom have said one phrase that had stuck with me a life time or those that have been continuously there. walks have helped and sport, or my mum telling me to focus on the birds when i was having a panic attack, and the rest of my family just being (see comments for next bit)

text:
ein liebes hallo in die runde - ich bin lilly, gründerin und initiatorin von #thebraveyoniproject 
geboren aus meiner eigenen lebensgeschichte und dem innigen wunsch, meine größte wunde in eine heilige wunde zu wandeln, erzählt #thebraveyoniproject die heldinnengeschichten tapferer, mutiger phönix-frauen, die ihrem lebensmärchen eine kraftvolle wendung verleihen, sich nicht länger von ihrem drachen im turm gefangen halten und vom schatten ihrer vergangenheit bestimmen lassen, sondern ihren drachen zähmen und selbstbestimmt, ermächtigt und lebendig auf seinem rücken hoch am himmel dem licht eines neuen morgens entgegenfliegen.
#thebraveyoniproject gebärt yoni-kunst für und mit frauen nach sexuellem missbrauch und gewalterfahrung körperlicher, psychischer und emotionaler art, nach komplikationsreichen schwangerschaften, traumatischen geburten, verletzungen des inneren mädchens auf ihrem weg zur frau uvm. 
die yonis werden liebevoll von hand gearbeitet, auf wunsch bemalt und gesegnet.
von herzen gern gebäre ich deine ganz persönliche yoni für dich! 
ich freu mich sehr auf deine nachricht an lilly@wuestenfrau.at ✨
mit viel liebe und vertrauen,
deine lilly

text_retweet:
powerful post! may the wounds heal. to the silent victims who wallow in pain, there’s hope. to those who’ve overcome, you inspire. #hyhup #holdyourheadup 
#repost @mynameisjessamyn with @get_repost
・・・
tw- sexual assault, rape.

i find the #metoo movement to be triggering as fuck. i’m in awe of its power, but it’s both absolutely necessary for our society and extremely painful, in equal measures. on one hand, i’m grateful for the cleansing power of the truth, and i’m inspired by the strength it takes my fellow survivors to gaze upon the the truth, especially in front of other people and especially when they’re directly confronting those who have harmed them. but on the other hand, reading/hearing about the trauma of others makes me miserable because it forces me to gaze upon my own truth which leads to a self-hate landslide from which recovery can feel impossible. and as much as i anticipate coming to terms with ‘the things i hate thinking about’ when i’m meditating or practicing yoga, i’m much less prepared to deal with my baggage when i’m innocently scrolling through social media feeds.

when i watched dr. ford’s testimony, all i could think was “i can’t believe she’s brave enough to talk about this in front of other people.” i was in awe. spellbound. talking about it on the international stage must be like living a nightmare. i wouldn’t know, as i can’t bring myself to do the same because my memories both horrify and embarrass me. and i’m well aware that i need not be embarrassed but that doesn’t make the emotions any less real.

i’m fascinated by the ways in which we all view/experience/hold our trauma. i wish sensitivity and empathy were considered as valuable as anger. surviving is more than just fodder for content. 
#ibelieveher #yoga 
@justincookphoto took this picture- my bra is by @thirdlove and my underwear is @savagexfenty

text_retweet:
#repost @philly_scoophall: here’s the story via @theshaderoom #sundycarter, who y’all might remember from #basketballwivesla, accused a man of drugging and raping her then leaking the video of the alleged assault on #instagram. she even went to the #losangelespolicedepartment and filed a police report.

it’s now being reported that the man she accused of assaulting her, #demetriusgreen, was arrested by police last month and he has been charged with revenge porn, the @blast reports. sundy is set to confront green, who is known as #philly comedian “meechie” on social media,  in court today in #philadelphia where he will be appearing on the charges.

the incident allegedly went down in philly, so sundy also met with law enforcement out there and filed an additional report. philly cops arrested green in relation to her allegation and he was charged with unlawful dissemination of an intimate image, possession of an instrument of crime with intent to employ it criminally, and harassment.

all charges were misdemeanors.

sundy said when green was arrested she never thought she would be part of the “#metoo movement.” “no one should ever be taken advantage of, whether it’s revenge porn or someone slipping a substance in your drink. unfortunately, i experienced this. i’ve pressed charges with hopes that justice will prevail,” she told the blast.

sources close to her are adamant she was also sexually assaulted by green, but the district attorney did not feel there was enough evidence to charge him for that.

he was given a bail of $2,500 and bonded out later the same day he was arrested, which was on september 21st.

there wasn’t any public comment available from green on his arrest but he has taken to social media in the past to deny the allegations made against him. .
.

text:
i’ve been experiencing a lot of “lady anger” lately, and it just keeps growing.  here’s the thing:
~ if she is drunk, that doesn’t automatically give you a right to her body.
~if she says no the first time or second time or third time, but you talk her into it anyway- she meant no the first time, and she’s probably not comfortable with what just happened.
~if she wears something you consider to be promiscuous, you do not have a right to her body.
~if she is your girlfriend, you do not have a right to her body.
~if she is your wife, you still do not have a right her body.
.
gentlemen, there is absolutely no point in time when you have a right to a woman’s body. ever.  the only time it’s okay touch a woman in any way is the point at which she gives you permission.  that’s it. there is no “but” and there is no grey area.  if you don’t have permission, the answer is no. feel free to pass that gem of knowledge on to your buddies. #realtalk

text:
day 15 since i’ve had any contact with my son and day “why won’t my dad call me” since noah’s had any contact with me.
~~~
as much as this sucks for me, without a doubt my biggest sadness is for noah... since september 3, 2016 i’ve spent almost every day with him.  i hate the constant instability and emotional chaos that he’s experiencing.  back to my zen spot...
~~~
this picture was from rosh hashana this year @templebetham .  they have the coolest kids services i’ve ever seen.  i really enjoy going to synagogue again.  noah loves the toy shofars.
~~~
i was listening to @joerogan today, and they were talking about how this is the age of communication and we’re still figuring all this shit out.  and we need to be nice to each other and take the time to listen to each other before jumping to conclusions.  essentially we need due process.
~~~
these extremists political movements are out of control.  we need rational, sane people to stand up for what’s right and speak just as loud as the extremes. “loudest wheel gets the grease”.
~~~
#metoo #believewomen #himtoo #falseaccusations #ilovemyboy #imissmyson

text_retweet:
this hits close to home today after a drs appt for my little. the dr was awesome and asked permission and gave an explanation before touching my little, as it should be. this is a great reminder these conversations start at home. 
#repost @sexpositive_families ・・・
anyone else encounter challenges with adult strangers or family members not respecting the body boundaries of the child you’re raising? they see a cute little face and feel entitled to put their hands, hugs or kisses all over them.... like one might do to a pet? 😒
.
well guess what!? you can absolutely intervene and advocate for a child’s rights, as a human being, to consent and body autonomy because children do not owe affection to anyone, not even to their parents/caregivers.
.
if we want the best chance for them to know that their body is theirs, not merely for others’ consumption or gratification... if we want to help minimize #metoo experiences that are based in consent violations, then speaking up to other adults when needed is how we can support the early consent education.
.
if you’re not sure what to say, something to the point can work best. “please do not touch (child’s name) without asking permission first. we are working hard to make sure they know about consent and that their body is theirs.” and if you have an infant or child whose communication may not be clearly expressed, again, just be direct, “please do not touch (child’s name) without asking me first. consent is important to us.”
.
and if the other adult is oppositional or challenges your response, that’s information that this is not someone who respects what you are doing and you can absolutely take steps to remove yourself and child from that situation. we do have choice, even when it feels like a tough choice.
.
children are not pets. they are humans who deserve the same respect often given to strangers. feel free to repost this if you need to send this message to folx in your world.
name: Uplift Parenting

text:
quiet as a mouse ii
30”x40”

the good ol’ boys club just wants women to be quiet, don’t speak up, don’t have a voice, don’t have independent thought and definitely don’t be in a power position. they want to keep you tied up and quiet. 
speak up. unite. demand equality. 
do not be silent! roar. 
arguably a top 5 indelible image and first cartoon character of our childhood years. 
minnie will never be the same. 
a mere part of a larger series of artworks that were to be, and are, my commentary on where it seems our country, society and culture is today compared to when i was a child. 
the crux of the series is based on childhood cartoons and characters that i had grown up with and that represent my childhood. now, these characters are distorted into something that will never, at least unlikely, be the same again. they used to be sharp, clean lines and brightly colored.... now they are rough, dirty, twisted and in black and white. 
i hope you like it. it is also a bit of therapy for me realizing a dealing with the state of our country right now.

i was assaulted at 8 years old in a mall.... i escaped miraculously. i was assaulted again at 19 in the street at night, walking by myself, i fought and run to meet my dad. i told him was happened and he tried to find the guy... no luck. i was almost raped by a coworker in a hotel in spain. when i tried to tell my boss she told me to say nothing, he was a pilot and i was going to get fired in a second. so i kept it to myself, like many of us other flight attendants. i never talked about these things before, why? shame. shame on us for being such whores. as much you think it’s hard for you guys, sorry, we still get it worse.

text:
خلال الفترة الماضية أقدم عدد لا بأس به من النساء الهنديات على الحديث بشكل علني وبشجاعة عن قصصهن مع التحرش الهندي، وكان من بينهن نساء ممن يعملن في مجال صناعة السينما الهندية،

#ايشواريا_راي أدلت بتصريحاتها الخاصة بقضية التحرش الجنسي أثناء مشاركتها في فاعلية للاحتفال بالإعلان رسميا عن شراكة جديدة بين ماركة لوريال باريس لمساحيق التجميل، وبين دار الأزياء الهندية التي أسسها مصمم الأزياء الهندي سابياساشي موخرجي 
ولقد حضرت آيشواريا الفاعلية التي أقيمت الثلاثاء بصفتها واحدة من سفيرات ماركة لوريال باريس، وأثناء مشاركتها في الفاعلية تحدثت آيشواريا عن قضية التحرش الجنسي، وظاهرة إقدام العديد من النساء الهنديات على مشاركة تجاربهن في التحرش الجنسي وقالت إن الهند أصبح لديها ما يشبه نسختها الخاصة من حركة " #metoo" الشهيرة والتي شاركت فيها الكثير من النساء الشهيرات من مختلف دول العالم بمشاركة قصصهن مع التحرش الجنسي لتسليط الضوء على هذه القضية الخطيرة وتشجيع النساء على الإبلاغ بما يتعرضن له من اعتداءات جنسية حتى لا يفلت الجناة بجرائمهم. 
آيشواريا راي 44 عام، قالت: "حركة #metoo أصبحت تحظى بشهرة كبيرة في الوقت الحالي، العالم أصبح أقرب ما يمكن الآن، بفضل مواقع التواصل الاجتماعي، وأصبح الصوت الواحد أكثر تأثيرا، من الرائع حقا أن نشاهد وسائل الإعلام تلتفت إلى هذه الأصوات التي تستحق أن يتم الاستماع إليها وإعطائها منصة، بعدها يمكن للقوانين في هذا البلد أن تتكفل بتحقيق العدالة"

وتابعت آيشواريا قائلة: "لا أعتقد أن التعليق على قضايا فردية بعينها أمر صحيح أو مسئول، ولكن علي أن أقول فليبارك الرب لهذه الأصوات وأن يمنحها المزيد من القوة، وأعتقد أن علينا منحها الدعم وعليكم (كوسائل إعلام) أن تتواجدوا من أجلها". .
.

#فن #اخبار_الفنانين #اخبار_الفن #الكويت #السعودية #عمان #قطر #الامارات #البحرين #احلام  #فديوهات #لبنان #سناب #مصر#فنانات #مشاهير #فنون #نجوم #اخبار #اخبار_المشاهير #المغرب #تونس #مصر #الجزائر#العراق

stop_filter_tweet: خلال الفترة الماضية أقدم عدد لا بأس به من النساء الهنديات على الحديث بشكل علني وبشجاعة عن قصصهن مع التحرش الهندي، وكان من بينهن نساء ممن يعملن في مجال صناعة السينما الهندية، أدلت بتصريحاتها الخاصة بقضية التحرش الجنسي أثناء مشاركتها في فاعلية للاحتفال بالإعلان رسميا عن شراكة جديدة بين ماركة لوريال باريس لمساحيق التجميل، وبين دار الأزياء الهندية التي أسسها مصمم الأزياء الهندي سابياساشي موخرجي ولقد حضرت آيشواريا الفاعلية التي أقيمت الثلاثاء بصفتها واحدة من سفيرات ماركة لوريال باريس، وأثناء مشاركتها في الفاعلية تحدثت آيشواريا عن قضية التحرش الجنسي، وظاهرة إقدام العديد من النساء الهنديات على مشاركة تجاربهن في التحرش الجنسي وقالت إن الهند أصبح لديها ما يشبه نسختها الخاصة من حركة `` الشهيرة والتي شاركت فيها الكثير من النساء الشهيرات من مختلف دول العالم بمشاركة قصصهن مع التحرش الجنسي لتسليط الضوء على هذه القضية الخطيرة وتشجيع النساء على الإبلاغ بما يتعرضن له من اعتداءات جنسية حتى لا يفلت الجناة بجرائمهم . آيشواريا راي 44 عام، قالت : `` حركة أصبحت تحظى بشهرة كبيرة في الوقت الحالي، العالم أصبح أقرب ما يمكن الآن، بفضل مواقع التواصل الاجتماعي، وأصبح الصوت الواحد أكثر تأثيرا، من الرائع حقا أن نشاهد وسائل الإعلام تلتفت إلى هذه الأصوات التي تستحق أن يتم الاستماع إليها وإعطائها منصة، بعدها يمكن للقوانين في هذا البلد أن تتكفل بتحقيق العدالة '' وتابعت آيشواريا قائلة : `` لا أعتقد أن التعليق على قضايا فردية بعينها أمر صحيح أو مسئول، ولكن علي أن أقول فليبارك الرب لهذه الأصوات وأن يمنحها المزيد من القوة، وأعتقد أن علينا منحها الدعم وعليكم ( كوسائل إعلام ) أن تتواجدوا من أجلها '' . . .

text: dirty little secret out in the open! anyway, i know i’m late for the suicide awareness and #metoo posts but better late than never right? i really fought myself for days about posting this but i think it needs to be told from a person like me (someone who you’d least expect this from). all throughout middle and high school this was a coping mechanism for me. a shitty one, yes. i know. back then life as i knew it was over. i didn’t have plans after i graduated because i didn’t really plan on graduating. i tried to take my life twice and failed twice. when i was (literally) 6, a guardian in my life had men coming in and out of the house at all odd hours of the night. she didn’t know what went down when she was doped up on drugs lmao. i was twelve when my dads friend came to the house (i was home from school bc sickness) and i don’t think i ever really recovered from that day. how can you? i mean time passes and you think about it less and less but then you smell his cologne or watch the same tv show that was on when he was over and the memories flood back and you can’t tell anyone because “jesus kat it was fucking 10 years ago” and “are you sure that’s what happened?” so you resort to this. and it’s shitty. it’s fucked up that me, a twelve year old, was too afraid to say “no” or “get out” because he had a knife. it ruined my childhood honestly. yeah he went to jail, but only because they found child porn on his computer. he got 1 year. no restraining order, no protection. 1 year and he was out and cruising up and down my street. this isn’t a “omg ur so courageous for sharing” post. this is a “this is why we don’t report” post. but you grow up. and you live. and learn. i will say though, i am about 2 1/2 years clean (sorry kenny) and you can hardly see the scars. it’s not a proud moment in my life and honestly if someone asked me i’d deny it. my main point is i know this is going to blow some of your minds that i used to do this..but just think who’s in your friend group right now doing it? who needs help and isn’t asking? you’re not alone. we all struggle. anyway thanks for coming to my ted talk

text:
yesterday was world mental health day and i debated all day about making this post, but i do believe it is important to raise awareness, so here it is... this summer jhonny and i debuted this routine, we said it was a routine dedicated to those who struggle with depression like me, but it was so much more than that, and it's more than what i will tell you here. this routine was about the struggles of our relationship due to my suicide attempts in 2017.

i'm literally shaking writing this, i was in a very dark place last year cause by many things. i described myself to friends as a full glass of water one more drop and the water would overflow. i lacked motivation for everything; waking up, going to work, dressing up, even dancing... i believed that i was holding everyone back and causing them pain with my pain and that everyone would be happier without me. i remember one night at hot bachata nights feeling really off, i walking about 100 laps around the dance floor wanting to leave wanting help but not knowing how, on that night i realized i lost who i was. after a panic attack and suicide attempt that same week i finally reached out to a therapist to get help. this was 1 year ago, i continue to struggle with depression but thanks to therapy and my loving husband who never gave up on me i am alive today and i no longer want to die.

i talks to women who have dealt with similar things in life as i have and they applaud me for going to therapy but always say i'm just not ready to start. don't get me wrong everyone has their own journey, but don't wait until it's too late, because i did, i brushed it off. i'm ok, i'm too busy, i dont have the money...
excuses that lead to a full glass of stress and a mental breakdown that made me think suicide was the best option, an option that didn't cross my mind the day before.
you are beautiful, your emotions are valid, you are enough, and it's ok to feel sad, i love you all and if you ever want to talk, any one of you, i will be happy to listen🖤
#worldmentalhealthday #metoo #youareenough #depression #anxiety #suicide #dancetherapy

text:
"i was sexually abused by my father as a small child. as a result, i have ptsd and suffer anxiety attacks, flashbacks and dissociation. i dissociated from the memories and grew up suffering anxiety attacks before i knew what they were. i was shut down and apathetic with no self awareness or drive to live. when something that is supposed to be delightful, exciting, sacred and beautiful is perverted and twisted into a skewed perception of forbidden pleasure, you feel utterly cheated.
-
the first time i had an orgasm, i had a horrible flashback of being forced to touch myself. that initial event sparked more flashbacks, causing more attacks and dissociation. i was too prideful to get help, so i turned to sex to remedy the issues.  i tried to replace the awful memories with good ones and took it pretty far. open relationships turned to swinging turned to orgies turned to drugs and lots of them. it was not a proud time in my life, but i'd be lying if i said it didn't help in that moment. my logic was that the more partners i had, the more i could associate positivity to the negative. i learned my triggers. i learned what i like and don't. i learned how to be an attentive, compassionate lover. i learned that i like it fast and rough, but also sickly sweet and slow. i learned that i can't have sex in the dark because i'll dissociate into that little molested girl. i learned that i can take all the precautionary measures and still have a flashback, so i have to have the confidence to say, "we need to stop. i had a flashback and i'm losing my sense of self." i learned that people will use your past against you, but that's not the norm. i learned that i like to be in control, but i also enjoy being handled so trust is of upmost importance in bed, which includes trusting each other's honesty even in the heat of the moment.
-
in the past, i've quietly spiraled into dissociation for fear of hurting someone's feelings. now i refuse to just 'get it over with,' and my therapist has helped me find that voice. i finally sought help a couple years ago and have been in therapy ever since."

text: (personal)((tw: sexual assault)) #cruel was difficult. it’s been a year and a week. i still have nightmares. it fucked my whole year up. my grades were painfully low and my mental health was at a more dangerous level than it had been in years. im still not comfortable talking openly about this (and still uncomfortable with the idea of posting this on facebook, but i can’t stand the political climate at the moment. if you know me, you know i’m not an angry person. but every time there’s an article or a meme or whatever on kavanaugh, i boil over inside. ignoring the whole case, which in itself is a monstrosity, the comments blaming women for their own fucking assaults make me feel a different kind of rage. one that stays like a pilot light in the pit of my stomach. i can feel it while i type. my assailant was never found. he’s still out there. he’s probably spouting comments akin to what i see kavanaugh supporters post on social media. my only hope is that he, in the midst of all the righteously angry women, feels the same fear and vulnerability that he made me feel.

text:
inspired by light | truth.
•
what 
women 
know:
all
must
rise.
•
today is international day of the girl and it feels important to me in a way i cannot wholly describe. it’s this thing about legacy that’s been up for me lately, as i track my own personal experience and present conversation among the collective amid the #metoo movement and how vital it is for women to rise a balanced feminine- not as “girl bosses” or uber radicalized. both, concepts ridiculous, as in my mind, their propagation feeds directly into the patriarchy, promoting egoic energy and a need to be in charge, through a forceful or domineering means. instead we can drop into our inherent feminine knowing and lead from a place of community, collaboration and conversation centered in compassion and creativity. we can be voices of reason, proponents for rationality, in that to be free, all must rise! all genders, all colors, all creeds need to break from suppressive paradigms that contribute to present, unfortunate reality. this. this is a legacy worthy. this is nobility. this is the way i wish to be, so that the girls and young women in my life can light torches of their own from the flames i have worked so hard to reclaim. carrying the light of their womanhood, wiser, stronger, balanced in power and reciprocity, beautiful voices for resounding change. 
_________
international day of the girl child is an international observance day declared by the united nations; it is also called the day of girls and the international day of the girl. october 11, 2012, was the first day of the girl child. the observation supports more opportunity for girls and increases awareness of gender inequality faced by girls worldwide based upon their gender. this inequality includes areas such as access to education, nutrition, legal rights, medical care, and protection from discrimination, violence against women and unfree child marriage.
_________
#internationaldayofthegirl #dayofthegirl #allrise  #weareformandlight #formandlight #wakeup #staywoke #awakeningspace #vibrationaldesigner  #vibrationaldesign  #vibrationalhealing

today is international day of the girl and it feels impoant to me in a way i cannot wholly describe. it’s this thing about legacy that’s been up for me lately, as i track my own personal experience and present conversation among the collective amid the  movement and how vital it is for women to rise a balanced feminine- not as “girl bosses” or uber radicalized. both, concepts ridiculous, as in my mind, their propagation feeds directly into the patriarchy, promoting egoic energy and a need to be in charge, through a forceful or domineering means. instead we can drop into our inherent feminine knowing and lead from a place of community, collaboration and conversation centered in compassion and creativity. we can be voices of reason, proponents for rationality, in that to be free, all must rise! all genders, all colors, all creeds need to break from suppressive paradigms that contribute to present, unfounate reality. this. this is a legacy wohy. this is nobility. this is the way i wish to be, so that the girls and young women in my life can light torches of their own from the flames i have worked so hard to reclaim. carrying the light of their womanhood, wiser, stronger, balanced in power and reciprocity, beautiful voices for resounding change. 
_________
international day of the girl child is an international observance day declared by the united nations; it is also called the day of girls and the international day of the girl. october 11, 2012, was the first day of the girl child. the observation suppos more oppounity for girls and increases awareness of gender inequality faced by girls worldwide based upon their gender. this inequality includes areas such as access to education, nutrition, legal rights, medical care, and protection from discrimination, violence against women and unfree child marriage.

secondo voi come si misura il consenso? è necessario creare una cultura attorno a questo argomento?

text:
#bookmail !! last month i put myself on a book buying ban and i did really well (only bought two books relevant to my research) so i’m planning to do the same this month: no book buying unless it’s for research and even then, only if it’s not available from the library. •
last week, in the muslim community, we had a bit of a stir when a popular religious leader made some very unfortunate comments regarding the kavanaugh debacle and the reasons why *islamically* he felt dr ford’s accusations could not be deemed credible. he went on to attempt to justify his position according to the quran. after a heated push back, he gave an “apology”. i’m not naming him, because i don’t want the conversation to be derailed by fanboys and fangirls, i really don’t care for personality politics. what i *would* like to draw attention to is this book by dr hina azam in which she analyses early islamic juristic writings on sexual violation punishable by law. it came up as a recommended read by a number of female muslim scholars, so of course i ordered it. will be sure to share snippets in stories!
•
#sexualviolationinislamiclaw #hinaazam #islamicstudies #islamicbooks #booksonislam #islamandgender

text:
🇫🇷⬇️ educar a mis hijas, lo hice una prioridad. me he dado cuenta que para enseñarles a ser libres, a pensar por sí mismos, tenía que dejar de lado muchas de mis opiniones y confrontarme diariamente con mi ego. al final,sigo aprendiendo cada días de ellas, me enseñan a ser madre. y luego ocurrió el #metoo , todos estos testimonios que me volvieron a colocar a mí situation de mujer en la sociedad, desde allí me di cuenta de que tenía que educar a las niñas, que tenían que transmitirles cosas que todavía  ninguna generación de mujeres había transmitido, cosas comunes como nunca encontrar normal sentirse presa de un hombre, o que su cuerpo es su propiedad absoluta y son las únicas que tienen poder sobre él, y tantas otras cosas que aún no he formulado. todo esto lo tengo que enseñar a ellas ahora mismo, aún que sean tan pequeñas.
en este día de sensibilización sobre la educación de las niñas, me digo que han tenido suerte nacer a francia y españa. gracias @planfrance por este día muy importante 🙏🏼 🇫🇷 éduquer mes filles, je m’en suis fait une priorité. je me suis rendu compte que pour leur apprendre à être libre, à penser par elles-même je devais mettre de côté beaucoup de mes opinions et me confronter quotidiennement à mon égo.  au final, j’apprends tout les jours à leurs côtés, elles m’éduquent à être mère. et puis il y a eu le #metoo , tous ces témoignages qui m’ont remis à ma place de femme dans la société, et là, je me suis rendu compte que j’avais des filles à éduquer, qu’il fallait leur transmettre des choses qu’aucune génération de femmes n’avait encore transmises, des choses banales comme de ne jamais trouver normal de se sentir une proie face à un homme, ou que leur corps est leur propriété absolue et qu’elles sont les seules à avoir des droits dessus,  et tellement d’autres choses que je n’ai pas encore formulées. tout ça doit s’apprendre tout de suite, alors qu’elles sont si petites. en ce jour de sensibilisation à l’éducation des filles, je me dis qu’elles ont de la chance d’être nées en france et en espagne. merci @planfrance pour ce jour important 🙏🏼 #education #enfance #niñas #mama #égalité #planfrance #fridakahlostyle #mesfilles #feminisme

text:
how have uk workplaces responded to the #metoo movement?
not that well according to a recent survey by law firm slater and gordon.
the survey of 2,000 women revealed 37% respondents had been sexually harassed at work in the last 12 months – and as well as being subjected to unwanted behaviour, 39% reported witnessing a colleague being harassed.
suggestive or inappropriate comments were the most common form of harassment according to the survey with 16% women receiving them, followed by sexually explicit or sexist conduct (11%) and 6% stating they’d been groped by a colleague.  #gurls #workplace #woman #entrepreneur #femaleentrepreneur

text:
happy #nationalcomingoutday
.
.
.

i was reminded yesterday of the harsh reality that for some, "coming out" can result in heartbreaking reactions in unexpected places. meanwhile, relative to where our country was on lgbtqai+ issues back when i was a kid, there's abundant evidence of progress.  and yet here we are in 2018, steeped in daily harsh reality data of where there's room for more progress (of course growth/progress never stops). as i reflect on national coming out day this year, i can't help but consider how #metoo, #whyididntreport, and other such truth-telling movements add to the scores of people who are "coming out" on-the-daily. (in many ways i don't think of "coming out" as something limited to the lgbtqai+ community). and do we ever have data around how these various forms of "coming out" result in heartbreak.  but they also open up so much opportunity for truth and healing and beauty and unification and even more progress.  and that's where i'll choose to focus.

#instagay #tbt#🌈 #carebears #cabbagepatchkids #gaykid #pride

text: älskar mitt jobb på ett klyschigt sätt, men också på ett brinnande feministiskt sätt. även om det är övermäktigt i bland med uppgiften att förändra destruktiva manlighetsnormer är det en djupt meningsfull sak att ägna dagarna åt. och ja, jag är såklart fed up på mäns våld, men jag tror samtidigt på förändring. vi måste tro på förändring. och det är ett privilegium att få arbeta med att förebygga våld. är väl medveten om det, och försöker tänka på alla grymma kvinnojoursaktivister, hbtq-aktivister, funkisförsvarare, asylrättsaktivister och människorättsförsvarare av alla slag varje dag. som kämpar närmare konsekvenserna av våldet. som stöttar utsatta dagligen. i grunden är den destruktiva manligheten orsaken till det mesta. så vi gör detta tillsammans! har varit i östersund och mött ett gäng aktivister från män, och deltagit i ett stormöte för män. det är sällsynt ovanligt att sitta i ett rum med bara män, och känna sig trygg. men det gör jag då och då i män-sammanhang. vår metod lilla rummet skapar en avskalad sårbarhet som är extremt ovanlig när män möts i grupp. jag har också fått magnifik utsikt, sova en natt på hotell, haft intensiva, fina jobbmöten med flera av mina favoritkollegor och vi har ätit musslor och druckit lite bubbel på vår lediga tid. så fint. nu rullar jag snart in i stockholm igen, speedad inför #metoo-perioden som komma skall. men peppad. nu jävlar kör vi! vi förändrar manligheten, ett steg i taget! 🙌

text:
new york city prosecutors have dropped one of six counts of sexual assault against harvey weinstein after the former movie mogul’s team questioned inconsistencies in a victim’s testimony.
.
the development, which was announced in a manhattan courtroom on thursday morning, involved an accusation of assault made by lucia evans, a once aspiring actress who told the new yorker that weinstein forced her to perform oral sex during a 2004 meeting.
.
weinstein surrendered to new york police in may and was charged with rape in the first degree, rape in the third degree and committing a criminal sexual act in the first degree for alleged forcible sexual acts against two women in 2004 and 2013, prosecutors have said.
.
in court thursday, manhattan asst. dist. atty. joan illuzi-osborn said the development would not affect the other five counts against weinstein.
.
wednesday’s development did not mark the first time the manhattan district attorney’s office has been questioned over its handling of sexual assault allegations against weinstein. earlier this year, new york gov. andrew cuomo ordered the state attorney general to review the office’s decision not to pursue charges against weinstein after he was accused of groping an italian model in 2015.
.
weinstein has been accused of sexual misconduct by more than 80 women, and the torrent of allegations against him served as the basis for the #metoo movement, which has led to the downfall of a number of celebrities and politicians.
.
(source: los angeles times, abc news)

text:
trauma is personal. it does not disappear if it is not validated. when it is ignored or invalidated the silent screams continue internally heard only by the one held captive. when someone enters the pain and hears the screams healing can begin
•
everyone heals differently. some choose to share their story and others choose to look forward instead of ahead. doesn’t make them any different from what they have been through. •
•

cruel••| day11 • "day for girl child"
ft the cruel indian neighbours who manage to have control on a girl's boundaries which when crossed can tear families. and these boundaries are as simple as the dressing, hairstyles and emotions, decisions. 
and no, a girl needn't get married by 21,22,23,24...what ever the fuck age you decide. she will when she feels she has to.
i'm really proud of how india has come from female foeticide to women playing major roles. parents now wish for baby girl(also a boy)  just the way they once did only for boys. the only thing that a father or a mother of a girl child are worried today isn't about how she is dressing or making friends from other gender. they are worried about what their neighbours, relatives, family friends,*the society* thinks. .
also, how not to be cruel,..
•focus on the body your saree shows off rather than on what her crop top shows.
• don't ask her to get married to a stranger and sleep with him.
• don't focus on how many guys she hangs out with. hangouts and hookups are different. 
i would say more but i am not jobless. 🥵
.

text:
it’s moments like right now, when i stop to take a look at what i am putting out in the world that i can’t help but feel my heart expanding with love, fierce courage, and purpose.
🤨
so in case you missed it, @refinedyxe has their latest issue out, where you can find my expert advice article about why holistic sexuality is the next step in living your best life, and the missing key to a happier, healthier world.
🤩
we all know and have heard time & time again how important it is to eat healthy and get some exercise - as it impacts your mental and emotional health in huge ways. i am here to tell you that just as important as these two aspects of our health truly is, so to is our sexuality.
💋
how we treat, think about, and touch ourselves, and how we teach kids to treat, think about, and touch themselves is shaping how we, and they, will show up in the world, for themselves and for others.
😍
why do you think that the #metoo movement exists, and where does rape culture stem from? i believe that this disconnection from ourselves, each other, and a healthy sexuality is a great place to start looking. let’s have these conversations about pleasure, consent, and boundaries, and understand that it first and foremost starts with you.

text: the #metoo movement, there is so much to say about it..two things i feel strongly about and want to bring up is 1. i’m hearing men are now scared, ummm ok let’s break that down a bit..first if you are coming from a place of respect and integrity, well then you have absolutely nothing to fear..but if your being smarmy yeah well then your going to  have to face that fear and change your ways. 2. let’s say you are a man who is respectful and has the utmost integrity towards women and your still scared? well pause for a minute and really deal with that fear...because that little bit of fear your feeling, turn it around and realize we women feel that every single fricken day of our lives...so i don’t know maybe you can take a bit of the fear and hold onto it for a bit, so that we can breathe...and for the record i am not a man hater...i love men, but for all of you who have stood idly by it’s time to stand with your sisters and speak the fuck up. time to not let the tribe mentality rule...we’ve got this. let’s love each other and ourselves just a bit more ❤️

text:
a couple of weeks ago i was guided to share one of my #metoo stories via social media, as i was overcome with inspiration by the courage of #drchristineblaseyford.

on #facebook many of my friends suggested i share it with a wider audience. one even requested that i send it to my senators.

i did both.

@elephantjournal asked me to publish my story to their now platform. 
and while they also changed tennis pro to athlete for fear of this man being identified (which really showcases why women have kept their stories silent for so long - there is so much invested in protecting those committing these acts!), i'm at peace knowing i've shared what i kept hidden for so long.

and that's only part of the story... go to my link in bio to read the full story.

and, i want to hear from you - comment on the story, share your story and the empowerment you've found from it. this is how we heal. this is how we rise up!

yours in love & empowerment, xo

#risingupforlove 
#whyididntreport 
#shareyourstory
#beempowered
#thisishowweheal
#elephantjournal

text:
"warrior daughter.
🔥
keep your gentleness, your open-flower heart, in a closed-up world.
🔥
there's such a thing as fierce grace. i'm learning the power of softness, when my instinct is to armour.
🔥
i'm telling my story, so you don't need to feel afraid of being different, or screwing up, or being scared to speak your truth.
🔥
i don't want you to learn the art of shrinking, and invisibility that i felt i needed so often.
🔥
be a force of nature, dear one.
be kali-tongued when it's needed.
be soft, but tolerate no motherf*ckery.
🔥
warrior daughter.
🔥
i want to be the kind of woman - soft, powerful, centred in her own skin and bone marrow - that can hold space for your becoming.
🔥
i honor you.
🔥
i honor all warrior mothers holding space for their warrior daughters.
🔥
we need your big hearts.
we need your bravery.
we need each other." ~ @mandylehto
.
📷 @patrickfore
.
.
#warriordaughter #risesisterrise #toleratenomotherfuckery #divinefeminine #rising #rewilding

text:
another gospel... my personal conviction. 
we are living in an hour where we are witnessing people moving on from what no longer works. another gospel is imperative. millennials don't go to church. they don't want church, and they can't comprehend church. we are attempting to shove ancient ideas into modern souls. if they aren't going to church, then do you think their children will go? now, what do you think the church will look like in 10 to 15 years? i'll answer, non-existent. pastors will have to find another trade because our tradition no longer works. church is moving out of the four walls and back into the hearts of men. millennials love god, but hate church... #metoo. 
i'm sorry but god is not the same yesterday, today, and forevermore. if this is true then why did he change with the times across scripture??? example: 
1. created a world with people, vegetation, and an animal kingdom, called it good / regrets creating the world with people, vegetation, and an animal kingdom and called it bad and destroyed his own creation.
2. in the ot god promised that his spirit will not always strive with man because we are only flesh / in the nt god (as jesus) says that he will be with us always, he will send a comforter (holy spirit) and that it will fall on all flesh!
3. god cuts a covenant with man with ceremonies, laws, stonings, and executions / in hebrews the writer confesses that god was unhappy with the former covenant because it was flawed and now he presents us with a new and better one. 
4. god allows men to have multiple wives / now we can only be husband of one wife. 
5. god once winked at ignorance / now he no longer does
6. god punished children for their father's sins / now because of christ you only are punished for your own sins, or not, because it's now under the blood. 
7. certain foods were a no-no if they came from an unclean animal (any animal with a split-hoof) / in acts god changes his mind and tells peter to eat all of the animals because nothing he made is common. 
8.  god allows incesteous behavior to populate and repopulate the earth / god decides incest is nasty, abominable, and sinful. (which it is very nasty)

text:
ignorance is bliss, they say and i can attest to it. .
i have been far at peace thinking the world is a great place - people love each other and are equal; wars, persecution and marginalization of minorities don't happen; all animals are treated kindly -sometimes, i even fantasize that everyone has turned vegetarian (😂); people understand the concept of waste generation and toxic waste and use reusuable steel cutlery; no one debates the effects of climate change; 'do you read?' is not a question to ask coz, of course, everyone reads; people invest as much time in learning as they do in debating to prove their point right... i could go on but you get the drift.
.
then i ask myself - would i rather be an ignorant fool who is naive about the world or would i rather be informed on what's happening and understand different perspectives. sadly, for my inner peace, i always pick the latter. and work on other ways to fix my view of the world and how i react to it.
.
(am still stuck on the accounts of harassment, violence and assault inflicted on all the people speaking up under #metoo. everything i read makes me want to cry).
.
why this picture, you ask? because, i can.

text:
as mum's we often think we are alone, going through the daily grind wondering why everyone else seems to have their shit together and coping so well when you are completely overwhelmed with everything that comes with being a mum, wife/partner, running a household, work etc all before even contemplating making anytime for that long soak in the bath or a decent hot cuppa.

having times when you sit and think what on earth was i thinking having kids and questioning whether you are cut out for all this mum milarky. 
wanting to throw the towel in and dreaming of packing a bag and jetting off to somewhere quiet, away from all of the requests, battles, tantrums, expectations and responsibility!

somewhere you can feel free again, away from the suffocation motherhood can bring.

wondering if it will ever get easier?
if the baby will ever sleep through or the toddler will ever just be happy with the jumper they originally asked for.
if your 5 year old will ever enjoy school or your 10 year old will actually ever listen to you?
will you ever be on time again? 
will you ever make any new friends, who will accept you and your brood in it's whole, crazy entirety?

i'm currently sitting on my loo pretending to poop to get 10mins to write this post, to let you know.................. me too! 
there is so much power in me too....
you feel out of your depth sometimes.......me too
you lose your shit sometimes.......me too (alot of the time actually)
sick of repeating yourself......me too
want to give up sometimes.......me too
feel suffocated sometimes.....me too
feel like you are obviously doing something wrong because everyone else copes just fine......... dya know what me too! 
see that mum always late to the playground, see that mum whose kid is having a melt down in the supermarket, see that mum who doesn't want to leave the house today, see that mum too tired to get dressed or do the housework, see that mum whose cuppa has gone cold again, see that mum smiling but really wants to scream and tell her.......me too because motherhood isnt easy and sometimes it only takes a simple me too, to help you feel like you are not alone, you are normal & it's ok!
#metoo #becomingmum

text: whenever i’m heading out to present, i have a routine before leaving my hotel room, because i need to banish the internalized demons of self-criticism, especially those that shame women and our bodies. so i stand in front of the mirror and i say (outloud): i look great! my butt looks great! i love my legs - they are strong and carry me around the world! i love my arms! they are strong and good for hugging. i look beautiful! and i go on an on a bit, talking to myself as if i were my own best friend, my biggest champion, who can see all the radiant parts of me better than anyone else. and i appreciate my internal and external beauty. because damn, those shaming patriarchal demons are vicious and even though i’ve done a ton of work to be aware of them and exorcize them, they still rear their evil voices. how do you deal with those demons? #resist #smashthepatriarchy

text:
💗international day of the girl💗
globally, 1 in 4 girls are married before they are 18, more than 62 million girls across the globe do not have access to education and there is (clearly) a lot of progress to be made when it comes to equal opportunities for women right here in the united states. my heart breaks because of the patriarchal world she must learn to live in-  but i know she's watching and reflecting my every move so i will continue to work to show her strength, confidence, resilience, the value of self worth and as much grace as possible as we move through this world. in a world of astronomical amounts of women coming forward with #metoo experiences, a mysogynistic president and women being paid less than men for the same jobs, i also must teach her how to fight for what she deserves, how to speak up and use her voice even when the world tells her to stay quiet and how to be big and bold, to take up space and to stand her ground even when the world tells her to stay small.

text: it is good to see more and more sexual harassment victims having the courage to face their perpetrators and speak out about the abuse they faced. however it is sad to see that if they're coming out after many years, a continuous question asked to them is ..why are they coming out now? why after all this time? is it for attention?it most certainly isn’t for attention and this is clear by the fact that these victims have stayed quiet for so long, suffering in silence. we forget to challenge the perpetrators and instead attack the victims. sexually abused victims don't have the courage to come out straightaway...they need time and support from people to face their assailant. especially if the person who abused them is a family member or a celebrity who has power and status. they might feel incredibly intimidated and afraid by their abusers. let’s not let the victims voices go  unheard! we need more courageous people like @chinmayisripaada so men in power will think twice before abusing women. #metoomovement  #justlisten #hearthemout #timesup #believewomen #womensreality #iamwithher #whyistayed #heforshe #yesallwomen #metoo #metoomovement #tamil #speakup #chinmayi

text:
just found out yesterday was national mental health day. i dream about the day i finally can share my story but for now all i can say is i’ve been to hell and back, i would wake up wondering if i wanted to make it through the rest of the day and go through the night wondering if i wanted to wake up the next morning, but thankfully god and the blessed mother was  always watching over me because i did survive and i made it to this day. everything that could possibly go wrong did, and i made some dumb decisions to cover up the pain, but i grew.  all i know is i’ve come to learn that everything happens for a reason, it’s just up to you if you will choose to use what had happened as a positive thing in your life or to let it keep bringing you down, . i soon hope to share my story to help anyone who has gone through what i have, but until then i’m glad and blessed to be able to say that i’ve made it this far, i survived, i’m here today, and so can you 💕 always remember those negative demons attacking your mind don’t have power unless you give it to them. obviously since i’m still not sharing my story shows that my healing process isn’t over it, it’s actually far from over but i’m so excited to see how much progress im going to make in the future and what opportunities will open along the way. 
i completely know what feeling absolutely alone feels like. i know what the rotting slowly and painfully inside feels like. i know what it feels like when you see, hear. smell something and it triggers a flashback. i know what the feeling of wantin to give up feels like and how hard it is to look past that at times. all i can say is do not stop fighting, know our power is much stronger than that and you still can survive and thrive. it is not too late always remember there’s always time to improve ❤️#nationalmentalhealthday .

text:
1 år sedan #metoo 💎 vad har hänt under året? vad borde ha hänt? hur går vi vidare? hur mår vi? hur gör vi så att ingen nånsin ska behöva säga "me too" igen?
lördagen den 20/10 klockan 12.00-14.00 håller vi en stillsam manifestation. vi samlar kraft, delar med oss av erfarenheter och fikar i sensus lokaler på skeppsbrogatan 47.

fram tills dess samlar vi också in berättelser om övergrepp i kalmarområdet. har du blivit utsatt för övergrepp eller trakasserier i kalmar? på en nattklubb, på jobbet, i skolan, på stan, i hemmet? för att belysa att sexuellt våld förekommer precis överallt, även i vår egen närmiljö, önskar vi att ni delar med er av era berättelser, antingen under #metookalmar eller genom att maila din berättelse till metoo@queensofkalmar.se. alla berättelser vi får in delas självklart anonymt om inget annat önskas. berättelserna läses upp under manifestationen lördagen den 20/10. jag hoppas vi ses då! ❤️🙌🏼

text:
” i don’t know one single woman who wants to be famous for having been assaulted” – chimamanda adichie on #metoo

nigerian author and feminist icon chimamanda ngozi adichie talked at the frankfurt book fair on tuesday and touched on the #metoo movement.

adichie said in the opening of the planet ’s biggest publishing event:

all around the world today women are speaking up. their tales are still not really heard. women continue to be invisible. women’s encounters continue to be invisible.

a year after the #metoo movement went viral and sparked a worldwide discussion about sexual harassment, adichie said there was much work left to be done.

it’s time for us to pay more than lip service to how women’s stories are for everybody.

we know from research that women read books by men and women. but guys read books by men. it’s time for men to read women.

she said:

we seem to live in a world where many people believe large numbers of women can simply wake up one day and make up stories about having been attacked.

i know many women who are interested in being famous. i don’t understand a single girl who wants to be famous for having been attacked.

text_retweet:
this image and caption from @sogayjen is so so important. white ladies, we gotta do better. smashing the patriarchy means smashing white supremacy, including the bits of it that have wormed their way into our brains. we’re not free until we’re all free. that’s how feminism is supposed to work. 
#repost @sogayjen
・・・
fellow white women: we have a very uncomfortable truth that we need to own up to. 
for too long, white women have taken shelter under the rule of white patriarchy. but doing so props up the very systems that oppress us, and leaves those who aren’t as protected as we are out in the cold. 
until we accept our long history of helping to uphold white supremacy and patriarchy, we cannot move forward. 
yes, it’s uncomfortable and sometimes painful to reflect on the ways we have stood as pillars of white supremacy and patriarchy. but challenging ourselves to look hard at the ways we contribute to a damaging system is the start of dismantling it.

so many cishet white women talk about smashing the patriarchy, but that can’t be done while ignoring your own privilege. it’s long past time for white people to interrogate the ways we’ve been complicit. 
in short: don’t be a susan collins. (note: i say fellow white ‘women’ even though i am nonbinary, for lack of better terminology. this fight has become very ‘men vs women,’ especially over the last few weeks, forgetting those who live outside that binary. i try to keep my language inclusive to folks of all genders, but i’m not perfect and have my own internalized shit to deal with. i’m open to dialogue about ways we can still fight for survivors and non-cis men in a more inclusive way, so any wisdom from those smarter than me is welcome!)
.
.
[image description: illustration of rebecca traister, with the text: “white women, who enjoy proximal power from their association with white men, have often served as the white patriarchy’s more eager foot soldiers.”]
#rebeccatraister #goodandmad  #checkyourprivilege #believesurvivors #believewomen #dissentispatriotic #callyourreps #ibelieveher #smashthepatriarchy #metoo #timesup #vote #feminist #feministart #artofinstagram #instaart #resistanceart #protestart

text: so today is mental health day and i post many photos about mental health but have never told my story. i feel confident enough in myself to share it with you and hopefully someone can relate or learn from it. since i was 12 i have been diagnosed with depression and i have been on antidepressants on and off since i was 16. this post is not to argue whether people should or should not take medication. i believe each individual should do what they believe is best for them and i am a huge fan of non-pharmacological interventions. anyway, it has been a long road full of highs, lows, and plateaus. i’ve learned a lot about myself and about putting yourself in others shoes as a result. i’m no where near perfect and still have bad days, but i found out what prevents and triggers those episodes. also what to do if i am having a bad day like eating a tub of icecream👅 my main point is no one knows what other people are going through so be kind and reach out if you think someone needs to talk💗 p.s this is my first time “coming out” on social media and is nerve wracking so please refrain from negative comments😊 #letstalkaboutmentalhealth #yournotalone #metoo
